value.title: Trump lambasts Lesley Stahl for pressing him on 'tough questions': 'That's no way to talk'
value.excerpt: President Trump, in a testy interview with CBS's Lesly Stahl, chastized the veteran reporter telling her "that's no way to talk" when she ribbed him about his ability to take "tough questions" during an interview meant to air on 60 Minutes on Sunday.

value.title: Trump guaranteed the election would be all about him
value.excerpt: Gallup on Thursday summed up his opponent’s fundamental problem: “The majority of U.S. registered voters, 56%, believe  Donald Trump does not deserve to be reelected, while 43% say he does.” That is a seven-point drop in his “deserves reelection” number taken in January.

value.title: Trump grants clemency to former Gary boxer Charles ‘Duke’ Tanner imprisoned for drug crimes
value.excerpt: Charles “Duke” Tanner, a former Gary boxer serving a 30-year sentence on federal drug and conspiracy convictions, was granted clemency Wednesday by President Donald Trump.

value.title: Ex-Trump aide Manafort beats Manhattan prosecutor's bid to revive NY fraud charges
value.excerpt: A New York appeals court on Thursday upheld the dismissal of state fraud charges against Paul Manafort, saying that reviving the case against U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman would violate double jeopardy rules.
